cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method for improving deep anomaly detection, which is a common problem in machine learning. The experiments involve natural language processing and vision tasks, indicating relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of generative models, which suggests relevance to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of robustness, which is relevant to sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
